HEADWORD: Cenotaph
<hw>Cen"o*taph</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧n"⟦osl⟧*t⟦adot⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>kenota`fion</grk>; <grk>keno`s</grk> empty +
<grk>ta`fos</grk> burial, tomb: cf. F.
<ets>c⟦eacute⟧notaphe</ets>.]</ety> <def>An empty tomb or a monument
erected in honor of a person who is buried elsewhere.</def>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>cenotaph</qex> in Westminster Abbey.</q>
